    <div class="row">
     <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 aboutus">
      <h2>
       <a class="noshowlink" name="aboutus">
        <span class="lang_about_us">
         About Us and Our Hospitals
        </span>
       </a>
      </h2>
      <span class="lang_aboutus_paragraphs_blurb">
       <p>
        The University of Chicago Medicine has been at the forefront of medical care since 1927. The medical center is part of the University of Chicago, an institution that consistently ranks among the 10 best universities in the world (Shanghai Index).
       </p>
       <p>
        Our more than 800 physicians are faculty members of the Pritzker School of Medicine, ranked regularly among the top medical schools in the United States (US News and World Report).
       </p>
       <p>
        We are also proud to say that 12 Nobel Prize winners in physiology or medicine have been affiliated with the University of Chicago Medicine.
       </p>
       <p>
        Our faculty and staff are dedicated to patient care, education and research, and the institution is supported by 9,500 employees, nearly 900 residents and fellows and more than 1,500 nurses.
       </p>
       <p>
        In 2013, the University of Chicago Medicine opened a new, state-of-the-art hospital, the Center for Care and Discovery.  The 10-story facility focuses on cancer, digestive diseases, neurosciences, advanced surgery and high-tech medical imaging. The hospital features 52 intensive care beds and 28 operating rooms, including a space for hybrid and robotic procedures.
       </p>
       <p>
        In addition to our adult hospital, the medical campus also includes the University of Chicago Medicine Comer Children’s Hospital, a 6-floor, 172-bed acute care facility that unites leading-edge technology with a family-centered, child-friendly philosophy to providing advanced care.
       </p>
      </span>
     </div>
    </div>
